.TH "Element.getAnimations" "JS" "July 18, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Element.getAnimations \- Element: getAnimations() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]getAnimations()\f[R] method of the \f[CR]Element\f[R]
interface (specified on the \f[CR]Animatable\f[R] mixin) returns an
array of all \f[CR]Animation\f[R] objects affecting this element or
which are scheduled to do so in future.
It can optionally return \f[CR]Animation\f[R] objects for descendant
elements too.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This array includes CSS Animations, CSS Transitions, and
Web Animations.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getAnimations()
getAnimations(options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An options object containing the following property:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]subtree\f[R]
A boolean value which, if \f[CR]true\f[R], causes animations that target
descendants of \f[I]Element\f[R] to be returned as well.
This includes animations that target any CSS pseudo\-elements attached
to \f[I]Element\f[R] or one of its descendants.
Defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
An \f[CR]Array\f[R] of \f[CR]Animation\f[R] objects, each representing
an animation currently targeting the \f[CR]Element\f[R] on which this
method is called, or one of its descendant elements if
\f[CR]{ subtree: true }\f[R] is specified.
.SH EXAMPLES
The following code snippet will wait for all animations on
\f[CR]elem\f[R] and its descendants to finish before removing the
element from the document.
.IP
.EX
Promise.all(
  elem.getAnimations({ subtree: \f[B]true\f[R] }).map((animation) \f[B]=>\f[R] animation.finished),
).then(() \f[B]=>\f[R] elem.remove());
.EE
